Polymorphism: Polymorphism is a combination of the following greek words (poly) and (morphisms). Poly means (many) and morphism means (ways to represent).
So polymorphism means doing one thing in many different ways. Polymorphism occurs during inheritance
Act of representing same thing in many different ways.

Question:
        How JVM knows which methods to call internally. As we know now it will call child class methods..
Answer:
        JVM knows by concept called Dynamic Method Dispatch (VVImportant).
        Dynamic Method Dispatch: It's a mechanism by which a call to an overridden method is resolved at runtime rather than at compile time.